<TEXT>
<P>
I was appalled to turn on my favorite late night news program "Nightline" (ABC, 
Dec. 3) and find Madonna and her video the evening's topic. 
</P>
<P>
I called KABC to complain and was further shocked when I was told my opinion 
was "a refreshing change" from the other calls the station was receiving. 
</P>
<P>
My complaint was simple. I objected to Channel 7's use of precious airtime of 
Madonna and her hardly news-worthy video. I was told most calls were complaints 
about morality. 
</P>
<P>
Why don't the news programs just keep us up to date on current crises and leave 
the trash to trash TV? 
</P>
<P>
Leslie Myrick, Los Angeles 
</P>
