<P>
As an older baby boomer, I read with interest "The Dead-End Kids." 
</P>
<P>
It occurred to me that you omitted the fastest way to climb the corporate 
ladder. It's called a variety of names: brown nosing, not making waves, company 
politics, networking -- anything to get that promotion. You know and I know the 
old adage: "It's not what you know, it's who you know." 
</P>
