<P>
Robert Hilburn's "20 Bands That Matter" (Dec. 2) was a brave attempt at the 
impossible. 
</P>
<P>
However, I feel one band in particular was served a major injustice by its 
exclusion: the Red Hot Chili Peppers. Faith No More are the new media darlings, 
and on their own are a powerful band, but anyone familiar with the 'Peppers' 
knows they are the true innovators of this style of music. 
</P>
<P>
I feel the R.H.C.P., who have taken so many chances musically over such a long 
period of time bringing together diverse musical influences were insulted by 
the inclusion of a band that blatantly rips them off. 
