<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHILIPPINE BATTLE KILLS 21 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Government troops battled communist rebels in the southern Philippines, leaving 
20 guerrillas and a soldier dead, a military report said Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121690-0050 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 322872 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 16, 1990, Sunday, Bulldog Edition 
</P>
