<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARRESTING WOMEN WHO SOLICIT DRINKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Most cities have operating budgets strained to the breaking point, violent 
crime is out of control and the police and Alcohol Beverage Control Commission 
guys are busting women in Santa Ana bars for soliciting men to buy them drinks 
("Bar Raids Net Women Who Allegedly Solicit Drinks," Dec. 9). 
</P>
<P>
This is the most stupid use of taxpayers' money that I have seen in a long 
time. 
</P>
<P>
And how about the buying male customers (Let's call them Dons -- not to be 
confused with Johns)? Are the police arresting and deporting them also? 
</P>
<P>
This law should be stripped from the books in Sacramento, and the enforcement 
money used for more constructive purposes, such as alcohol and drug 
rehabilitation and drunk-driving enforcement. 
</P>
<P>
BOB CONSTANTINE, Placentia 
</P>
