<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: THE REGION; 
</P>
<P>
VOTER REGISTRATION DEADLINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dec. 24 is the deadline to register to vote in the Jan. 22 special election for 
the 1st District seat on the Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors. 
</P>
<P>
Those over the age of 18 who live in the district -- which stretches from El 
Sereno and Lincoln Heights, east to Irwindale and La Puente and southeast to 
Santa Fe Springs -- can obtain voter registration applications at post offices, 
county offices and many banks. 
</P>
<P>
The county Registrar of Voters also will mail registration applications to 
anyone who telephones (213) 721-1100. 
</P>
<P>
Although the registration deadline is Dec. 24, voter applications will be 
accepted by mail in the registrar's office until Dec. 28, said registrar 
spokeswoman Marcia Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
If no candidate receives more than 50% of the vote in the Jan. 22 election, the 
top two finishers will face off in a Feb. 19 runoff. The close of registration 
for that contest will be Jan. 22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
