<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: LA PUENTE; 
</P>
<P>
DIVISION OF LOT APPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A bid to increase the salability of a lot containing a vacant Gemco department 
store, a Unocal service station and 771 empty parking spaces has won City 
Council approval. 
</P>
<P>
The council Tuesday voted unanimously approve an application by the landowner, 
La Puente-Beverly Road Assn., to divide the lot into three parcels, one large 
and two small. 
</P>
<P>
Rick Hartmann, the city's planning and community development director, said 
subdividing the lot will encourage prospective buyers by increasing the 
flexibility of development. 
</P>
<P>
The Gemco store has been vacant since late 1986, and the gas station is the 
only business operating on the 12.83-acre site along Hacienda Boulevard north 
of Francisquito Avenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
