<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOT THE SHORTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In references to Her World, Dec. 2: Dec. 13 is not the shortest day of the 
year. It is the day with the earliest sunset. The shortest day is about a week 
later and the latest sunrise is in early January. 
</P>
<P>
W. J. RADKE 
</P>
<P>
Seattle 
</P>
</TEXT>
