<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WOOLRIDGE PACES SANTA ANA TO THIRD VICTORY IN A ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chauncey Woolridge scored 20 points to lead Santa Ana High School to a 72-48 
victory over Cypress in a nonleague basketball game Saturday night at Santa 
Ana. Woolridge, a 6-foot-5 senior, also had 17 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
The victory was the third in a row for Santa Ana (3-2), which led 31-19 at the 
half and 55-35 after three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
In other nonlegaue games: 
</P>
<P>
Estancia 66, Mission Viejo 45 -- Matt Fuerbringer scored 22 points as Estancia 
(8-1) came back a night after losing in the championship game of the La Quinta 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Savanna 75, Bellarmine Jefferson 26 -- Point guard Jeremy Lyche had 15 points 
and 12 rebounds and Toby Priest added 12 points as host Savanna routed 
Bell-Jeff of Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
Baptist Christian 58, Liberty Christian 57 (OT) -- Gabe Baltodano of Liberty 
Christian made two free throws with six seconds left to send the game into 
overtime. Dave Kellams led Liberty Christian (3-4) with 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
In the third-place game of the El Dorado tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Canyon Country Canyon 79, Anaheim Canyon 62 -- Reggie Haggans scored 19 points 
to lead Canyon Country Canyon. Anaheim Canyon lead, 17-15, after the first 
quarter but was outscored, 20-9, in the second. 
</P>
<P>
Pomona defeated Long Beach Jordan, 77-64, to win the tournament title. 
</P>
<P>
In the consolation championship: 
</P>
<P>
Sunny Hills 86, Downey 68 -- David Ragsdale scored 25 points and Brett 
Mitchelson added 24 for Sunny Hills, which led, 22-14, after the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
In the seventh-place game: 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 76, Whittier Christian 58 -- David Robichaaud and Brett Tomko each 
scored 24 points for El Dorado. 
</P>
<P>
In the Beverly Hills tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 79, El Toro 59 -- Ken Koppelman and Jason Senik each scored 14 
for El Toro (4-3) in the third-place game. 
</P>
