SKATEBOARDERS SKIRT MILAN TRAFFIC BAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MILAN, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Enterprising Christmas shoppers used skateboards here Saturday when this city 
closed its business center to cars and trucks to combat pollution. 
</P>
<P>
Others took to the streets on horses, bicycles and on foot. The City Council 
said the ban would be in force both Saturday and today for 12 hours daily. 
</P>
<P>
Pollution levels have been above locally set limits for the past three days. It 
is the third successive winter that authorities have banned traffic to reduce 
pollution. 
