<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Love Christmas, but hate shopping? Want the kids to see Santa without you 
having to hear the jingling of cash registers? 
</P>
<P>
Then head to Wilmington on Sunday for the third annual Harbor Holidays Parade. 
</P>
<P>
More than 100 floats and bands, some from as far away as Santa Margarita, will 
parade along with some 2,100 marchers. 
</P>
<P>
The event starts about 1 p.m. on M Street near Avalon Boulevard, winds its way 
to Pacific Coast Highway and ends at Banning Park. The sponsor is Wilmington's 
Chamber of Commerce. 
