<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MASTER'S UPSETS UC SAN DIEGO, 90-83 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Led by Stu Epperson with a team-high 22 points, The Master's College upset UC 
San Diego, 90-83, in a men's nonconference basketball game at Master's on 
Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Master's shot 57% from the field to hand UCSD, ranked No. 3 in NCAA Division 
III, its first loss of the year. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Bruner scored 17 points and Ryan Farrell added 14 for Master's (6-4). 
</P>
<P>
Epperson made eight of 11 shots from the field and four of four attempts from 
the free-throw line to lead the Mustangs. 
</P>
<P>
Tim Rapp scored a game-high 32 points for UCSD but made just 11 of 26 
field-goal attempts. 
</P>
<P>
UCSD fell to 7-1. 
</P>
